comments: Trent Jr. (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position on Dort (OKC) and cleanly dislodges the ball. Any contact as they both pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.  After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Trent Jr. steps out of bounds stands.
During the drive, Trent Jr. (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position on Dort (OKC) and cleanly dislodges the ball.
Bazley (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact created by Trent Jr. (TOR) at the end of the drive.
Trent Jr. (TOR) makes contact with Maledon's (OKC) arm, which affects his ability to maintain full control of the ball.
Birch (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact created by Maledon (OKC) at the end of the drive.
Birch (TOR) places two resting hands on Maledon's (OKC) back and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect his ability to maintain a legal guarding position.
During the rebound, Birch (TOR) makes clean ball contact as he tries to tip it away from Roby (OKC).
A timeout is granted to the Raptors within 5 seconds and before the inbounds pass.
Replay review of the foul called on Boucher (TOR) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Boucher (TOR) makes contact with Dort's (OKC) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) avoids making contact with Trent Jr.'s (TOR) arm as he tries to poke the ball loose.
Birch (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Dort's (OKC) path and absorbs the contact.
Bazley (OKC) is in the paint for about three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
During the screen, Flynn (TOR) and Maledon (OKC) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Pokusevski (OKC) commits a take foul on Watanabe (TOR).
Boucher (TOR) cleanly intercepts the inbounds pass and any contact with Bazley (OKC) as he returns to the ground is deemed incidental.
